                <div class="policy-section" id="introduction">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> 1. Introduction</h2>
                    <p>Welcome to SEOTuber! This app provides SEO tools for YouTube creators, including title generation, keyword research, SEO scoring, and tag extraction. We prioritize your privacy and are transparent about how we handle your information. This policy explains what data we collect, why we collect it, how it's used, and your rights. <strong>By using SEOTuber, you agree to this policy.</strong></p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="information-collected">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-database"></i> 2. Information We Collect</h2>
                    <h3>User-Provided Information:</h3>
                    <div class="features-grid">
                        <div class="feature-card">
                            <h4><i class="fas fa-heading"></i> Titles & Keywords Tab</h4>
                            <p>Topics, keywords, and related terms you input for analysis</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="feature-card">
                            <h4><i class="fas fa-key"></i> Keyword Research Tab</h4>
                            <p>Topics for generating keywords, volume, and competition data</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="feature-card">
                            <h4><i class="fas fa-check-square"></i> SEO Checker Tab</h4>
                            <p>YouTube video URLs you submit for SEO scoring</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="feature-card">
                            <h4><i class="fas fa-tags"></i> Extractor Tab</h4>
                            <p>YouTube video URLs you submit for tag extraction</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <h3>Automatically Collected Information:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Device & Usage Data:</strong> IP address, device type, OS, browser, app usage frequency, features accessed, timestamps, errors/crashes</li>
                        <li><strong>Advertising Data:</strong> Data related to ads served (e.g., ad views, clicks) via third-party ad networks</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h3>Information from YouTube:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><em>Only</em> publicly available data (titles, descriptions, tags, view counts, engagement metrics) from the <strong>public YouTube videos</strong> whose URLs you submit</li>
                        <li>We <strong>do not</strong> access private YouTube account data or private videos</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="how-we-use">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> 3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>To provide, operate, and improve SEOTuber's features</li>
                        <li>To analyze usage trends and optimize app performance</li>
                        <li>To display relevant advertisements (our primary revenue source)</li>
                        <li>To respond to support requests</li>
                        <li>To prevent, detect, and address fraud, security, or technical issues</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="misuse-safeguards">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> 4. Potential Misuse & Safeguards</h2>
                    <p>We anticipate these risks and implement safeguards:</p>
                    
                    <div class="highlight">
                        <h3>Risk: Unauthorized Data Collection/Selling</h3>
                        <p><strong>Safeguard:</strong> We <strong>do not sell your personal data or specific inputs</strong> (topics, keywords, URLs) to third parties. Aggregated, anonymized data may be used for analytics or shared with advertisers.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="highlight">
                        <h3>Risk: Profiling for Targeted Ads Based on Sensitive Topics</h3>
                        <p><strong>Safeguard:</strong> Ad networks may use general categories, but we <strong>do not</strong> share your specific, sensitive inputs directly with advertisers.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="highlight">
                        <h3>Risk: Accidental Exposure of Private Videos</h3>
                        <p><strong>Safeguard:</strong> The SEO Checker and Extractor <strong>only function with PUBLIC YouTube video URLs</strong>. Entering a private/unlisted URL will result in an error.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="highlight">
                        <h3>Risk: Ad Networks Over-Collecting Data</h3>
                        <p><strong>Safeguard:</strong> We use reputable ad networks compliant with industry standards. You can opt-out of personalized ads via device settings.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="disclaimer">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> 5. Accuracy Disclaimer & User Responsibility</h2>
                    <div class="warning">
                        <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i>
                        <div>
                            <h3>Accuracy of Data</h3>
                            <p>The volume and competition data provided in the "Keyword" tab are estimates based on available data and algorithms. <strong>We do not guarantee 100% accuracy</strong> of this data. SEO results depend on many factors beyond our control.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="warning">
                        <i class="fas fa-user-shield"></i>
                        <div>
                            <h3>User Responsibility</h3>
                            <p>You agree to use SEOTuber responsibly and in compliance with YouTube's Terms of Service and all applicable laws. <strong>You are solely responsible for any misuse of the app</strong>, including but not limited to:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Using the app for spamming, black-hat SEO, or any deceptive practices</li>
                                <li>Violating copyright or intellectual property rights</li>
                                <li>Inputting any illegal, harmful, or offensive content</li>
                                <li>Relying solely on the app's output without independent verification</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>We reserve the right to terminate access to users who misuse the app.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="third-party">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-handshake"></i> 6. Third-Party Sharing</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Ad Networks:</strong> Essential for displaying ads. They collect data to serve relevant ads and measure effectiveness.</li>
                        <li><strong>Analytics Providers:</strong> Help us understand usage patterns (data is aggregated and anonymized).</li>
                        <li><strong>Cloud Service Providers:</strong> Store data securely (e.g., AWS, Google Cloud).</li>
                        <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> If required by law, court order, or to protect our rights/safety.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="data-security">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> 7. Data Security</h2>
                    <p>We employ technical and organizational measures (encryption, access controls, audits) to protect your data. However, <strong>no online transmission or storage is 100% secure</strong>. We cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="data-retention">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-history"></i> 8. Data Retention</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>User Inputs (Topics, Keywords, URLs):</strong> Typically retained temporarily (30-90 days) for functionality and debugging, then deleted or anonymized</li>
                        <li><strong>Analytics/Usage Data:</strong> Retained longer (1-2 years) in aggregated form for trend analysis</li>
                        <li><strong>Account Data (if applicable in future):</strong> Retained while your account is active + a reasonable period afterward</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="children">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-child"></i> 9. Children's Privacy</h2>
                    <p>SEOTuber is <strong>not intended for children under 13</strong>. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided data, contact us immediately for deletion.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="international">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-globe"></i> 10. International Transfers</h2>
                    <p>Data may be processed/stored outside your country (e.g., in the USA). We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place per applicable laws.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="your-rights">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-user-check"></i> 11. Your Rights</h2>
                    <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
                        <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                        <li>Request deletion of your data (subject to legal limitations)</li>
                        <li>Opt-out of certain data processing (like personalized ads)</li>
                        <li>Withdraw consent (if processing was based on consent)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Contact us (see below) to exercise these rights.</strong></p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="policy-section" id="changes">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-sync-alt"></i> 12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
                    <p>We may update this policy. Significant changes will be notified within the app or via email (if applicable). The "Last Updated" date will reflect changes. Continued use signifies acceptance.</p>
                </div>
                
